# Data persistence

| Topic | Rule |
|-------|------|
| Backends | `DB_TYPE` in `environment.ts`: `sqlite` \| `postgres`. Behavior differs — **sqlite** uses extra Kysely plugins (boolean/json) in `database.ts`. |
| `Database` type | All tables appear on the `Database` interface in `src/features-system/data-persistence/database.ts` + matching plugins per dialect. |
| New table | Add `*Schema.ts` + `*Repo.ts` under the feature `data/`, migration in `src/features-system/data-persistence/migrations/`, then `pnpm migrate:latest` (or `:dev`). |
| Windows | `migrate.ts` uses a **custom** `FileMigrationProvider` (file-URL fix). Preserve it when changing migration loading. |
| SQL home | Keep queries in repos; keep Discord handlers thin (see `.cursor/rules/elegance.mdc`). |

Architecture reference: **`AGENTS.md`**.
